{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So, a big question that we're facing now"},{"time":3000,"text":"and have been for quite a number of years now:"},{"time":6000,"text":"are we at risk of a nuclear attack?"},{"time":9000,"text":"Now, there's a bigger question"},{"time":11000,"text":"that's probably actually more important than that,"},{"time":14000,"text":"is the notion of permanently eliminating"},{"time":18000,"text":"the possibility of a nuclear attack,"},{"time":20000,"text":"eliminating the threat altogether."},{"time":22000,"text":"And I would like to make a case to you that"},{"time":25000,"text":"over the years since we first developed atomic weaponry,"},{"time":28000,"text":"until this very moment,"},{"time":30000,"text":"we've actually lived in a dangerous nuclear world"},{"time":33000,"text":"that's characterized by two phases,"},{"time":36000,"text":"which I'm going to go through with you right now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":39000,"text":"First of all, we started off the nuclear age in 1945."},{"time":43000,"text":"The United States had developed a couple of atomic weapons"},{"time":45000,"text":"through the Manhattan Project,"},{"time":47000,"text":"and the idea was very straightforward:"},{"time":49000,"text":"we would use the power of the atom"},{"time":51000,"text":"to end the atrocities and the horror"},{"time":53000,"text":"of this unending World War II"},{"time":55000,"text":"that we'd been involved in in Europe and in the Pacific."},{"time":58000,"text":"And in 1945,"},{"time":61000,"text":"we were the only nuclear power."},{"time":63000,"text":"We had a few nuclear weapons,"},{"time":65000,"text":"two of which we dropped on Japan, in Hiroshima,"},{"time":67000,"text":"a few days later in Nagasaki, in August 1945,"},{"time":70000,"text":"killing about 250,000 people between those two."}]},{"cues":[{"time":73000,"text":"And for a few years,"},{"time":75000,"text":"we were the only nuclear power on Earth."},{"time":78000,"text":"But by 1949, the Soviet Union had decided"},{"time":82000,"text":"it was unacceptable to have us as the only nuclear power,"},{"time":85000,"text":"and they began to match what the United States had developed."},{"time":89000,"text":"And from 1949 to 1985"},{"time":92000,"text":"was an extraordinary time"},{"time":95000,"text":"of a buildup of a nuclear arsenal"},{"time":98000,"text":"that no one could possibly have imagined"},{"time":100000,"text":"back in the 1940s."},{"time":102000,"text":"So by 1985 -- each of those red bombs up here"},{"time":105000,"text":"is equivalent of a thousands warheads --"},{"time":108000,"text":"the world had"},{"time":110000,"text":"65,000 nuclear warheads,"},{"time":113000,"text":"and seven members of something"},{"time":115000,"text":"that came to be known as the \"nuclear club.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":118000,"text":"And it was an extraordinary time,"},{"time":120000,"text":"and I am going to go through some of the mentality"},{"time":122000,"text":"that we -- that Americans and the rest of the world were experiencing."},{"time":125000,"text":"But I want to just point out to you that 95 percent"},{"time":128000,"text":"of the nuclear weapons at any particular time"},{"time":131000,"text":"since 1985 -- going forward, of course --"},{"time":133000,"text":"were part of the arsenals"},{"time":135000,"text":"of the United States and the Soviet Union."},{"time":138000,"text":"After 1985, and before the break up of the Soviet Union,"},{"time":141000,"text":"we began to disarm"},{"time":143000,"text":"from a nuclear point of view."},{"time":145000,"text":"We began to counter-proliferate,"},{"time":147000,"text":"and we dropped the number of nuclear warheads in the world"},{"time":149000,"text":"to about a total of 21,000."},{"time":152000,"text":"It's a very difficult number to deal with,"},{"time":153000,"text":"because what we've done is"},{"time":155000,"text":"we've quote unquote \"decommissioned\" some of the warheads."},{"time":158000,"text":"They're still probably usable. They could be \"re-commissioned,\""},{"time":160000,"text":"but the way they count things, which is very complicated,"},{"time":163000,"text":"we think we have about a third"},{"time":165000,"text":"of the nuclear weapons we had before."},{"time":167000,"text":"But we also, in that period of time,"},{"time":169000,"text":"added two more members to the nuclear club:"},{"time":171000,"text":"Pakistan and North Korea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":174000,"text":"So we stand today with a still fully armed nuclear arsenal"},{"time":178000,"text":"among many countries around the world,"},{"time":180000,"text":"but a very different set of circumstances."},{"time":182000,"text":"So I'm going to talk about"},{"time":185000,"text":"a nuclear threat story in two chapters."},{"time":187000,"text":"Chapter one is 1949 to 1991,"},{"time":190000,"text":"when the Soviet Union broke up,"},{"time":192000,"text":"and what we were dealing with, at that point and through those years,"},{"time":195000,"text":"was a superpowers' nuclear arms race."},{"time":198000,"text":"It was characterized by"},{"time":200000,"text":"a nation-versus-nation,"},{"time":202000,"text":"very fragile standoff."},{"time":204000,"text":"And basically,"},{"time":206000,"text":"we lived for all those years,"},{"time":208000,"text":"and some might argue that we still do,"},{"time":210000,"text":"in a situation of"},{"time":212000,"text":"being on the brink, literally,"},{"time":214000,"text":"of an apocalyptic, planetary calamity."},{"time":218000,"text":"It's incredible that we actually lived through all that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":221000,"text":"We were totally dependent during those years"},{"time":223000,"text":"on this amazing acronym, which is MAD."},{"time":226000,"text":"It stands for mutually assured destruction."},{"time":229000,"text":"So it meant"},{"time":231000,"text":"if you attacked us, we would attack you"},{"time":233000,"text":"virtually simultaneously,"},{"time":235000,"text":"and the end result would be a destruction"},{"time":237000,"text":"of your country and mine."},{"time":239000,"text":"So the threat of my own destruction"},{"time":241000,"text":"kept me from launching"},{"time":243000,"text":"a nuclear attack on you. That's the way we lived."},{"time":247000,"text":"And the danger of that, of course, is that"},{"time":249000,"text":"a misreading of a radar screen"},{"time":252000,"text":"could actually cause a counter-launch,"},{"time":254000,"text":"even though the first country had not actually launched anything."},{"time":257000,"text":"During this chapter one,"},{"time":259000,"text":"there was a high level of public awareness"},{"time":261000,"text":"about the potential of nuclear catastrophe,"},{"time":264000,"text":"and an indelible image was implanted"},{"time":266000,"text":"in our collective minds"},{"time":268000,"text":"that, in fact, a nuclear holocaust"},{"time":270000,"text":"would be absolutely globally destructive"},{"time":273000,"text":"and could, in some ways, mean the end of civilization as we know it."},{"time":276000,"text":"So this was chapter one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":279000,"text":"Now the odd thing is that even though"},{"time":281000,"text":"we knew that there would be"},{"time":283000,"text":"that kind of civilization obliteration,"},{"time":286000,"text":"we engaged in America in a series --"},{"time":288000,"text":"and in fact, in the Soviet Union --"},{"time":290000,"text":"in a series of response planning."},{"time":292000,"text":"It was absolutely incredible."},{"time":294000,"text":"So premise one is we'd be destroying the world,"},{"time":296000,"text":"and then premise two is, why don't we get prepared for it?"},{"time":299000,"text":"So what"},{"time":301000,"text":"we offered ourselves"},{"time":303000,"text":"was a collection of things. I'm just going to go skim through a few things,"},{"time":305000,"text":"just to jog your memories."},{"time":307000,"text":"If you're born after 1950, this is just --"},{"time":309000,"text":"consider this entertainment, otherwise it's memory lane."}]},{"cues":[{"time":312000,"text":"This was Bert the Turtle. (Video)"},{"time":330000,"text":"This was basically an attempt"},{"time":332000,"text":"to teach our schoolchildren"},{"time":334000,"text":"that if we did get engaged"},{"time":336000,"text":"in a nuclear confrontation and atomic war,"},{"time":339000,"text":"then we wanted our school children"},{"time":341000,"text":"to kind of basically duck and cover."},{"time":343000,"text":"That was the principle. You --"},{"time":345000,"text":"there would be a nuclear conflagration"},{"time":347000,"text":"about to hit us, and if you get under your desk,"},{"time":349000,"text":"things would be OK."}]},{"cues":[{"time":351000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":353000,"text":"I didn't do all that well"},{"time":355000,"text":"in psychiatry in medical school, but I was interested,"},{"time":357000,"text":"and I think this was seriously delusional."}]},{"cues":[{"time":360000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":362000,"text":"Secondly, we told people"},{"time":364000,"text":"to go down in their basements"},{"time":366000,"text":"and build a fallout shelter."},{"time":368000,"text":"Maybe it would be a study when we weren't having an atomic war,"},{"time":371000,"text":"or you could use it as a TV room, or, as many teenagers found out,"},{"time":374000,"text":"a very, very safe place for a little privacy with your girlfriend."},{"time":377000,"text":"And actually -- so there are multiple uses of the bomb shelters."},{"time":380000,"text":"Or you could buy a prefabricated bomb shelter"},{"time":383000,"text":"that you could simply bury in the ground."},{"time":385000,"text":"Now, the bomb shelters at that point --"},{"time":387000,"text":"let's say you bought a prefab one -- it would be a few hundred dollars,"},{"time":389000,"text":"maybe up to 500, if you got a fancy one."},{"time":391000,"text":"Yet, what percentage of Americans"},{"time":393000,"text":"do you think ever had a bomb shelter in their house?"},{"time":395000,"text":"What percentage lived in a house with a bomb shelter?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":398000,"text":"Less than two percent. About 1.4 percent"},{"time":401000,"text":"of the population, as far as anyone knows,"},{"time":403000,"text":"did anything,"},{"time":405000,"text":"either making a space in their basement"},{"time":407000,"text":"or actually building a bomb shelter."},{"time":410000,"text":"Many buildings, public buildings, around the country --"},{"time":412000,"text":"this is New York City -- had these little civil defense signs,"},{"time":415000,"text":"and the idea was that you would"},{"time":417000,"text":"run into one of these shelters and be safe"},{"time":419000,"text":"from the nuclear weaponry."},{"time":421000,"text":"And one of the greatest governmental delusions"},{"time":424000,"text":"of all time was something that happened"},{"time":426000,"text":"in the early days of"},{"time":428000,"text":"the Federal Emergency Management Agency, FEMA, as we now know,"},{"time":431000,"text":"and are well aware of their behaviors from Katrina."},{"time":434000,"text":"Here is their first big public"},{"time":437000,"text":"announcement."},{"time":439000,"text":"They would propose --"},{"time":441000,"text":"actually there were about six volumes written on this --"},{"time":443000,"text":"a crisis relocation plan"},{"time":445000,"text":"that was dependent upon"},{"time":447000,"text":"the United States having three to four days warning"},{"time":450000,"text":"that the Soviets were going to attack us."},{"time":452000,"text":"So the goal was to evacuate the target cities."},{"time":455000,"text":"We would move people out of the target cities"},{"time":457000,"text":"into the countryside."}]},{"cues":[{"time":459000,"text":"And I'm telling you, I actually testified at the Senate"},{"time":462000,"text":"about the absolute ludicrous idea"},{"time":465000,"text":"that we would actually evacuate,"},{"time":466000,"text":"and actually have three or four days' warning."},{"time":468000,"text":"It was just completely off the wall."},{"time":470000,"text":"Turns out that they had another idea"},{"time":473000,"text":"behind it, even though this was --"},{"time":475000,"text":"they were telling the public it was to save us."},{"time":477000,"text":"The idea was that we would force the Soviets"},{"time":479000,"text":"to re-target their nuclear weapons -- very expensive --"},{"time":482000,"text":"and potentially double their arsenal,"},{"time":484000,"text":"to not only take out the original site,"},{"time":486000,"text":"but take out sites where people were going."},{"time":489000,"text":"This was what apparently, as it turns out, was behind all this."},{"time":492000,"text":"It was just really, really frightening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":495000,"text":"The main point here is we were dealing with"},{"time":497000,"text":"a complete disconnect from reality."},{"time":500000,"text":"The civil defense programs were disconnected"},{"time":503000,"text":"from the reality of what we'd see in all-out nuclear war."},{"time":505000,"text":"So organizations like Physicians for Social Responsibility,"},{"time":509000,"text":"around 1979, started saying this a lot publicly."},{"time":512000,"text":"They would do a bombing run. They'd go to your city,"},{"time":515000,"text":"and they'd say, \"Here's a map of your city."},{"time":517000,"text":"Here's what's going to happen if we get a nuclear hit.\""},{"time":520000,"text":"So no possibility of medical response to,"},{"time":522000,"text":"or meaningful preparedness for"},{"time":524000,"text":"all-out nuclear war."},{"time":526000,"text":"So we had to prevent nuclear war"},{"time":528000,"text":"if we expected to survive."},{"time":530000,"text":"This disconnect was never actually resolved."},{"time":533000,"text":"And what happened was --"},{"time":535000,"text":"when we get in to chapter two"},{"time":537000,"text":"of the nuclear threat era,"},{"time":540000,"text":"which started back in 1945."}]},{"cues":[{"time":542000,"text":"Chapter two starts in 1991."},{"time":544000,"text":"When the Soviet Union broke up,"},{"time":546000,"text":"we effectively lost that adversary"},{"time":548000,"text":"as a potential attacker of the United States, for the most part."},{"time":551000,"text":"It's not completely gone. I'm going to come back to that."},{"time":553000,"text":"But from 1991"},{"time":555000,"text":"through the present time,"},{"time":557000,"text":"emphasized by the attacks of 2001,"},{"time":559000,"text":"the idea of an all-out nuclear war"},{"time":562000,"text":"has diminished and the idea of a single event,"},{"time":565000,"text":"act of nuclear terrorism"},{"time":567000,"text":"is what we have instead."},{"time":569000,"text":"Although the scenario has changed"},{"time":572000,"text":"very considerably, the fact is"},{"time":574000,"text":"that we haven't changed our mental image"},{"time":576000,"text":"of what a nuclear war means."},{"time":578000,"text":"So I'm going to tell you what the implications of that are in just a second."},{"time":581000,"text":"So, what is a nuclear terror threat?"},{"time":583000,"text":"And there's four key ingredients to describing that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586000,"text":"First thing is that the global nuclear weapons,"},{"time":589000,"text":"in the stockpiles that I showed you in those original maps,"},{"time":591000,"text":"happen to be not uniformly secure."},{"time":594000,"text":"And it's particularly not secure"},{"time":596000,"text":"in the former Soviet Union, now in Russia."},{"time":598000,"text":"There are many, many sites where warheads are stored"},{"time":601000,"text":"and, in fact, lots of sites where fissionable materials,"},{"time":604000,"text":"like highly enriched uranium and plutonium,"},{"time":607000,"text":"are absolutely not safe."},{"time":609000,"text":"They're available to be bought, stolen, whatever."},{"time":612000,"text":"They're acquirable, let me put it that way."},{"time":615000,"text":"From 1993 through 2006,"},{"time":618000,"text":"the International Atomic Energy Agency"},{"time":620000,"text":"documented 175 cases of nuclear theft,"},{"time":623000,"text":"18 of which involved highly enriched uranium or plutonium,"},{"time":627000,"text":"the key ingredients to make a nuclear weapon."},{"time":631000,"text":"The global stockpile of highly enriched uranium"},{"time":634000,"text":"is about 1,300, at the low end,"},{"time":636000,"text":"to about 2,100 metric tons."},{"time":639000,"text":"More than 100 megatons of this"},{"time":641000,"text":"is stored in particularly insecure"},{"time":644000,"text":"Russian facilities."},{"time":647000,"text":"How much of that do you think it would take"},{"time":649000,"text":"to actually build a 10-kiloton bomb?"},{"time":651000,"text":"Well, you need about 75 pounds of it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655000,"text":"So, what I'd like to show you"},{"time":658000,"text":"is"},{"time":660000,"text":"what it would take to hold 75 pounds"},{"time":663000,"text":"of highly enriched uranium."},{"time":666000,"text":"This is not a product placement. It's just --"},{"time":668000,"text":"in fact, if I was Coca Cola, I'd be pretty distressed about this --"},{"time":670000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":673000,"text":"-- but"},{"time":675000,"text":"basically, this is it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":678000,"text":"This is what you would need to steal or buy"},{"time":681000,"text":"out of that 100-metric-ton stockpile"},{"time":683000,"text":"that's relatively insecure"},{"time":685000,"text":"to create the type of bomb"},{"time":687000,"text":"that was used in Hiroshima."},{"time":689000,"text":"Now you might want to look at plutonium"},{"time":691000,"text":"as another fissionable material that you might use in a bomb."},{"time":694000,"text":"That -- you'd need 10 to 13 pounds of plutonium."},{"time":698000,"text":"Now, plutonium, 10 to 13 pounds:"},{"time":701000,"text":"this. This is enough plutonium"},{"time":704000,"text":"to create a Nagasaki-size atomic weapon."},{"time":709000,"text":"Now this situation, already I --"},{"time":711000,"text":"you know, I don't really like thinking about this,"},{"time":714000,"text":"although somehow I got myself a job"},{"time":716000,"text":"where I have to think about it. So"},{"time":718000,"text":"the point is that we're very, very insecure"},{"time":721000,"text":"in terms of developing this material."},{"time":724000,"text":"The second thing is, what about the know-how?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":726000,"text":"And there's a lot of controversy about"},{"time":728000,"text":"whether terror organizations have the know-how"},{"time":731000,"text":"to actually make a nuclear weapon."},{"time":734000,"text":"Well, there's a lot of know-how out there."},{"time":736000,"text":"There's an unbelievable amount of know-how out there."},{"time":739000,"text":"There's detailed information on how to assemble"},{"time":741000,"text":"a nuclear weapon from parts."},{"time":744000,"text":"There's books about how to build a nuclear bomb."},{"time":747000,"text":"There are plans for how to create a terror farm"},{"time":750000,"text":"where you could actually manufacture and develop"},{"time":752000,"text":"all the components and assemble it."},{"time":755000,"text":"All of this information is relatively available."},{"time":758000,"text":"If you have an undergraduate degree in physics,"},{"time":760000,"text":"I would suggest --"},{"time":762000,"text":"although I don't, so maybe it's not even true --"},{"time":764000,"text":"but something close to that would allow you,"},{"time":766000,"text":"with the information that's currently available,"},{"time":768000,"text":"to actually build a nuclear weapon."}]},{"cues":[{"time":772000,"text":"The third element of the nuclear terror threat"},{"time":776000,"text":"is that, who would actually do such a thing?"},{"time":779000,"text":"Well, what we're seeing now is a level of terrorism"},{"time":782000,"text":"that involves individuals who are highly organized."},{"time":785000,"text":"They are very dedicated and committed."},{"time":787000,"text":"They are stateless."},{"time":789000,"text":"Somebody once said, Al Qaeda"},{"time":791000,"text":"does not have a return address,"},{"time":793000,"text":"so if they attack us with a nuclear weapon,"},{"time":795000,"text":"what's the response, and to whom is the response?"},{"time":798000,"text":"And they're retaliation-proof."},{"time":800000,"text":"Since there is no real retribution possible"},{"time":803000,"text":"that would make any difference,"},{"time":805000,"text":"since there are people willing to actually give up their lives"},{"time":808000,"text":"in order to do a lot of damage to us,"},{"time":810000,"text":"it becomes apparent"},{"time":812000,"text":"that the whole notion"},{"time":814000,"text":"of this mutually assured destruction would not work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":816000,"text":"Here is Sulaiman Abu Ghaith,"},{"time":818000,"text":"and Sulaiman was a key lieutenant of Osama Bin Laden."},{"time":821000,"text":"He wrote many, many times statements to this effect:"},{"time":823000,"text":"\"we have the right to kill four million Americans,"},{"time":826000,"text":"two million of whom should be children.\""},{"time":828000,"text":"And we don't have to go overseas"},{"time":830000,"text":"to find people willing to do harm, for whatever their reasons."},{"time":832000,"text":"McVeigh and Nichols, and the Oklahoma City attack"},{"time":835000,"text":"in the 1990s"},{"time":837000,"text":"was a good example of homegrown terrorists."},{"time":839000,"text":"What if they had gotten their hands on a nuclear weapon?"},{"time":841000,"text":"The fourth element"},{"time":843000,"text":"is that the high-value U.S. targets"},{"time":845000,"text":"are accessible, soft and plentiful."}]},{"cues":[{"time":848000,"text":"This would be a talk for another day, but the level of the preparedness"},{"time":850000,"text":"that the United States has achieved"},{"time":852000,"text":"since 9/11 of '01"},{"time":854000,"text":"is unbelievably inadequate."},{"time":856000,"text":"What you saw after Katrina"},{"time":858000,"text":"is a very good indicator"},{"time":860000,"text":"of how little prepared the United States is"},{"time":863000,"text":"for any kind of major attack."},{"time":865000,"text":"Seven million ship cargo containers"},{"time":867000,"text":"come into the United States every year."},{"time":869000,"text":"Five to seven percent only are inspected --"},{"time":872000,"text":"five to seven percent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":875000,"text":"This is Alexander Lebed,"},{"time":878000,"text":"who was a general that worked with Yeltsin,"},{"time":880000,"text":"who talked about, and presented to Congress,"},{"time":883000,"text":"this idea that the Russians had developed --"},{"time":886000,"text":"these suitcase bombs. They were very low yield --"},{"time":888000,"text":"0.1 to one kiloton,"},{"time":891000,"text":"Hiroshima was around 13 kilotons --"},{"time":893000,"text":"but enough to do an unbelievable amount of damage."},{"time":896000,"text":"And Lebed came to the United States"},{"time":898000,"text":"and told us that many, many --"},{"time":901000,"text":"more than 80 of the suitcase bombs"},{"time":903000,"text":"were actually not accountable."},{"time":905000,"text":"And they look like this. They're basically very simple arrangements."},{"time":907000,"text":"You put the elements into a suitcase."},{"time":910000,"text":"It becomes very portable."},{"time":912000,"text":"The suitcase can be conveniently dropped"},{"time":914000,"text":"in your trunk of your car."},{"time":916000,"text":"You take it wherever you want to take it, and you can detonate it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":918000,"text":"You don't want to build a suitcase bomb,"},{"time":921000,"text":"and you happen to get one of those insecure"},{"time":923000,"text":"nuclear warheads that exist."},{"time":925000,"text":"This is the size of"},{"time":927000,"text":"the \"Little Boy\" bomb that was dropped at Hiroshima."},{"time":929000,"text":"It was 9.8 feet long,"},{"time":931000,"text":"weighed 8,800 pounds. You go down to"},{"time":933000,"text":"your local rent-a-truck"},{"time":936000,"text":"and for 50 bucks or so,"},{"time":938000,"text":"you rent a truck that's got the right capacity,"},{"time":940000,"text":"and you take your bomb,"},{"time":942000,"text":"you put it in the truck and you're ready to go."},{"time":945000,"text":"It could happen. But what it would mean and who would survive?"},{"time":948000,"text":"You can't get an exact number for that kind of probability,"},{"time":951000,"text":"but what I'm trying to say is that"},{"time":953000,"text":"we have all the elements of that happening."},{"time":955000,"text":"Anybody who dismisses the thought"},{"time":957000,"text":"of a nuclear weapon"},{"time":959000,"text":"being used by a terrorist is kidding themselves."}]},{"cues":[{"time":961000,"text":"I think there's a lot of people in the intelligence community --"},{"time":964000,"text":"a lot of people who deal with this work in general"},{"time":967000,"text":"think it's almost inevitable, unless we do certain things"},{"time":970000,"text":"to really try to defuse the risk,"},{"time":973000,"text":"like better interdiction, better prevention,"},{"time":975000,"text":"better fixing, you know, better screening"},{"time":977000,"text":"of cargo containers that are coming into the country and so forth."},{"time":980000,"text":"There's a lot that can be done to make us a lot safer."},{"time":983000,"text":"At this particular moment,"},{"time":985000,"text":"we actually could end up"},{"time":987000,"text":"seeing a nuclear detonation in one of our cities."},{"time":990000,"text":"I don't think we would see an all-out nuclear war"},{"time":993000,"text":"any time soon, although even that is not completely off the table."},{"time":996000,"text":"There's still enough nuclear weapons"},{"time":998000,"text":"in the arsenals of the superpowers"},{"time":1000000,"text":"to destroy the Earth many, many times over."},{"time":1003000,"text":"There are flash points in India and Pakistan,"},{"time":1006000,"text":"in the Middle East, in North Korea,"},{"time":1008000,"text":"other places where the use of nuclear weapons,"},{"time":1011000,"text":"while initially locally,"},{"time":1013000,"text":"could very rapidly"},{"time":1015000,"text":"go into a situation"},{"time":1017000,"text":"where we'd be facing all-out nuclear war."},{"time":1020000,"text":"It's very unsettling."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1023000,"text":"Here we go. OK."},{"time":1025000,"text":"I'm back in my truck, and we drove over the Brooklyn Bridge."},{"time":1028000,"text":"We're coming down,"},{"time":1030000,"text":"and we bring that truck"},{"time":1032000,"text":"that you just saw"},{"time":1034000,"text":"somewhere in here, in the Financial District."},{"time":1048000,"text":"This is a 10-kiloton bomb,"},{"time":1051000,"text":"slightly smaller than was used"},{"time":1053000,"text":"in Hiroshima. And I want to just conclude this"},{"time":1056000,"text":"by just giving you some information. I think --"},{"time":1058000,"text":"\"news you could use\" kind of concept here."},{"time":1061000,"text":"So, first of all, this would be horrific"},{"time":1063000,"text":"beyond anything we can possibly imagine."},{"time":1065000,"text":"This is the ultimate."},{"time":1067000,"text":"And if you're in the half-mile radius"},{"time":1069000,"text":"of where this bomb went off,"},{"time":1071000,"text":"you have a 90 percent chance of not making it."},{"time":1073000,"text":"If you're right where the bomb went off,"},{"time":1075000,"text":"you will be vaporized. And that's --"},{"time":1077000,"text":"I'm just telling you, this is not good."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1079000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1081000,"text":"You assume that."},{"time":1083000,"text":"Two-mile radius, you have a 50 percent chance"},{"time":1086000,"text":"of being killed,"},{"time":1088000,"text":"and up to about eight miles away --"},{"time":1090000,"text":"now I'm talking about killed instantly --"},{"time":1092000,"text":"somewhere between a 10 and 20 percent"},{"time":1094000,"text":"chance of getting killed."},{"time":1096000,"text":"The thing about this is that"},{"time":1098000,"text":"the experience of the nuclear detonation is --"},{"time":1102000,"text":"first of all, tens of millions of degrees Fahrenheit"},{"time":1105000,"text":"at the core here, where it goes off,"},{"time":1107000,"text":"and an extraordinary amount of energy"},{"time":1109000,"text":"in the form of heat, acute radiation"},{"time":1112000,"text":"and blast effects."},{"time":1114000,"text":"An enormous hurricane-like wind,"},{"time":1116000,"text":"and destruction of buildings almost totally,"},{"time":1119000,"text":"within this yellow circle here."},{"time":1121000,"text":"And what I'm going to focus on, as I come to conclusion here,"},{"time":1123000,"text":"is that, what happens to you"},{"time":1126000,"text":"if you're in here?"},{"time":1128000,"text":"Well, if we're talking about the old days"},{"time":1130000,"text":"of an all-out nuclear attack,"},{"time":1132000,"text":"you, up here,"},{"time":1133000,"text":"are as dead as the people here. So it was a moot point."},{"time":1136000,"text":"My point now, though, is that there is a lot"},{"time":1138000,"text":"that we could do for you who are in here,"},{"time":1140000,"text":"if you've survived the initial blast."},{"time":1142000,"text":"You have, when the blast goes off --"},{"time":1144000,"text":"and by the way, if it ever comes up, don't look at it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1146000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1148000,"text":"If you look at it, you're going to be blind,"},{"time":1150000,"text":"either temporarily or permanently."},{"time":1152000,"text":"So if there's any way that you can avoid,"},{"time":1154000,"text":"like, avert your eyes, that would be a good thing."},{"time":1157000,"text":"If you find yourself alive, but"},{"time":1159000,"text":"you're in the vicinity of a nuclear weapon,"},{"time":1162000,"text":"you have -- that's gone off --"},{"time":1164000,"text":"you have 10 to 20 minutes, depending on the size"},{"time":1166000,"text":"and exactly where it went off,"},{"time":1168000,"text":"to get out of the way before"},{"time":1170000,"text":"a lethal amount of radiation"},{"time":1172000,"text":"comes straight down from the mushroom cloud that goes up."},{"time":1175000,"text":"In that 10 to 15 minutes, all you have to do --"},{"time":1177000,"text":"and I mean this seriously --"},{"time":1179000,"text":"is go about a mile"},{"time":1181000,"text":"away from the blast."},{"time":1183000,"text":"And what happens is -- this is --"},{"time":1185000,"text":"I'm going to show you now some fallout plumes. Within 20 minutes,"},{"time":1187000,"text":"it comes straight down. Within 24 hours,"},{"time":1189000,"text":"lethal radiation is going out with prevailing winds,"},{"time":1192000,"text":"and it's mostly in this particular direction --"},{"time":1194000,"text":"it's going northeast."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1196000,"text":"And if you're in this vicinity, you've got to get away."},{"time":1199000,"text":"So you're feeling the wind --"},{"time":1201000,"text":"and there's tremendous wind now"},{"time":1203000,"text":"that you're going to be feeling -- and you want to go"},{"time":1205000,"text":"perpendicular to the wind"},{"time":1207000,"text":"[not upwind or downwind]."},{"time":1209000,"text":"if you are in fact able to see where the blast was in front of you."},{"time":1212000,"text":"You've got to get out of there."},{"time":1214000,"text":"If you don't get out of there, you're going to be exposed"},{"time":1216000,"text":"to lethal radiation in very short order."},{"time":1218000,"text":"If you can't get out of there,"},{"time":1220000,"text":"we want you to go into a shelter and stay there."},{"time":1223000,"text":"Now, in a shelter in an urban area means"},{"time":1226000,"text":"you have to be either in a basement as deep as possible,"},{"time":1229000,"text":"or you have to be on a floor -- on a high floor --"},{"time":1232000,"text":"if it's a ground burst explosion, which it would be,"},{"time":1235000,"text":"higher than the ninth floor. So you have to be tenth floor or higher,"},{"time":1237000,"text":"or in the basement."},{"time":1240000,"text":"But basically, you've got to get out of town as quickly as possible."},{"time":1243000,"text":"And if you do that,"},{"time":1245000,"text":"you actually can survive a nuclear blast."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1249000,"text":"Over the next few days to a week,"},{"time":1251000,"text":"there will be a radiation cloud,"},{"time":1253000,"text":"again, going with the wind, and settling down"},{"time":1255000,"text":"for another 15 or 20 miles out --"},{"time":1257000,"text":"in this case, over Long Island."},{"time":1259000,"text":"And if you're in the direct fallout zone here,"},{"time":1262000,"text":"you really have to either be sheltered or you have to get out of there,"},{"time":1264000,"text":"and that's clear. But if you are sheltered,"},{"time":1267000,"text":"you can actually survive."},{"time":1269000,"text":"The difference between knowing information"},{"time":1271000,"text":"of what you're going to do personally,"},{"time":1273000,"text":"and not knowing information, can save your life,"},{"time":1275000,"text":"and it could mean the difference between"},{"time":1277000,"text":"150,000 to 200,000 fatalities"},{"time":1279000,"text":"from something like this"},{"time":1282000,"text":"and half a million to 700,000 fatalities."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1285000,"text":"So, response planning in the twenty-first century"},{"time":1288000,"text":"is both possible and is essential."},{"time":1290000,"text":"But in 2008, there isn't one single American city"},{"time":1294000,"text":"that has done effective plans"},{"time":1296000,"text":"to deal with a nuclear detonation disaster."},{"time":1299000,"text":"Part of the problem is that"},{"time":1301000,"text":"the emergency planners themselves, personally,"},{"time":1303000,"text":"are overwhelmed psychologically by the thought"},{"time":1305000,"text":"of nuclear catastrophe."},{"time":1307000,"text":"They are paralyzed."},{"time":1309000,"text":"You say \"nuclear\" to them, and they're thinking,"},{"time":1311000,"text":"\"Oh my God, we're all gone. What's the point? It's futile.\""},{"time":1314000,"text":"And we're trying to tell them, \"It's not futile."},{"time":1316000,"text":"We can change the survival rates"},{"time":1318000,"text":"by doing some commonsensical things.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1321000,"text":"So the goal here is to minimize fatalities."},{"time":1324000,"text":"And I just want to leave you with the personal points"},{"time":1326000,"text":"that I think you might be interested in."},{"time":1328000,"text":"The key to surviving a nuclear blast"},{"time":1330000,"text":"is getting out,"},{"time":1332000,"text":"and not going into harm's way."},{"time":1335000,"text":"That's basically all we're going to be talking about here."},{"time":1337000,"text":"And the farther you are away in distance,"},{"time":1340000,"text":"the longer it is in time"},{"time":1342000,"text":"from the initial blast;"},{"time":1344000,"text":"and the more separation between you"},{"time":1346000,"text":"and the outside atmosphere, the better."},{"time":1348000,"text":"So separation -- hopefully with dirt or concrete,"},{"time":1351000,"text":"or being in a basement --"},{"time":1353000,"text":"distance and time is what will save you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1355000,"text":"So here's what you do. First of all,"},{"time":1357000,"text":"as I said, don't stare at the light flash,"},{"time":1359000,"text":"if you can. I don't know you could possibly resist doing that."},{"time":1361000,"text":"But let's assume, theoretically, you want to do that."},{"time":1363000,"text":"You want to keep your mouth open, so your eardrums"},{"time":1365000,"text":"don't burst from the pressures."},{"time":1368000,"text":"If you're very close to what happened, you actually do have to duck and cover,"},{"time":1371000,"text":"like Bert told you, Bert the Turtle."},{"time":1373000,"text":"And you want to get under something so that you're not injured"},{"time":1376000,"text":"or killed by objects, if that's at all possible."},{"time":1378000,"text":"You want to get away from the initial fallout mushroom cloud,"},{"time":1380000,"text":"I said, in just a few minutes."},{"time":1382000,"text":"And shelter and place. You want to move [only]"},{"time":1385000,"text":"crosswind for 1.2 miles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1387000,"text":"You know, if you're out there and you see buildings horribly destroyed"},{"time":1390000,"text":"and down in that direction,"},{"time":1392000,"text":"less destroyed here,"},{"time":1394000,"text":"then you know that it was over there, the blast, and you're going this way,"},{"time":1396000,"text":"as long as you're going crosswise to the wind."},{"time":1400000,"text":"Once you're out and evacuating,"},{"time":1402000,"text":"you want to keep as much of your skin,"},{"time":1404000,"text":"your mouth and nose covered, as long as that covering"},{"time":1406000,"text":"doesn't impede you moving and getting out of there."},{"time":1409000,"text":"And finally, you want to get decontaminated as soon as possible."},{"time":1412000,"text":"And if you're wearing clothing, you've taken off your clothing,"},{"time":1414000,"text":"you're going to get showered down some place"},{"time":1416000,"text":"and remove the radiation that would be --"},{"time":1418000,"text":"the radioactive material that might be on you."},{"time":1421000,"text":"And then you want to stay in shelter for 48 to 72 hours minimum,"},{"time":1425000,"text":"but you're going to wait hopefully -- you'll have your little wind-up,"},{"time":1427000,"text":"battery-less radio,"},{"time":1429000,"text":"and you'll be waiting for people to tell you"},{"time":1431000,"text":"when it's safe to go outside. That's what you need to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1433000,"text":"In conclusion,"},{"time":1435000,"text":"nuclear war is less likely than before,"},{"time":1437000,"text":"but by no means out of the question, and it's not survivable."},{"time":1440000,"text":"Nuclear terrorism is possible -- it may be probable --"},{"time":1443000,"text":"but is survivable."},{"time":1445000,"text":"And this is Jack Geiger, who's one of the heroes"},{"time":1447000,"text":"of the U.S. public health community."},{"time":1450000,"text":"And Jack said the only way to deal"},{"time":1452000,"text":"with nuclear anything,"},{"time":1454000,"text":"whether it's war or terrorism,"},{"time":1456000,"text":"is abolition of nuclear weapons."},{"time":1458000,"text":"And you want something to work on once you've fixed global warming,"},{"time":1461000,"text":"I urge you to think about the fact that"},{"time":1463000,"text":"we have to do something about this"},{"time":1465000,"text":"unacceptable, inhumane"},{"time":1467000,"text":"reality of nuclear weapons"},{"time":1469000,"text":"in our world."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1471000,"text":"Now, this is my favorite civil defense slide, and I --"},{"time":1473000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":1475000,"text":"-- I don't want to be indelicate, but"},{"time":1477000,"text":"this --"},{"time":1479000,"text":"he's no longer in office. We don't really care, OK."},{"time":1482000,"text":"This was sent to me by somebody"},{"time":1484000,"text":"who is an aficionado of civil defense procedures,"},{"time":1487000,"text":"but the fact of the matter is that"},{"time":1489000,"text":"America's gone through a very hard time."},{"time":1491000,"text":"We've not been focused, we've not done what we had to do,"},{"time":1494000,"text":"and now we're facing the potential of"},{"time":1497000,"text":"bad, hell on Earth."},{"time":1499000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}